A jet of flames burst from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki set fire to a specific patch of the forest, then circled above, observing for a moment. Oddly, as it had slowed down, the strange sounds of cries behind it had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thraki before!"
" My flight is very different. I don't let myself be roughly lifted by a huge pink dragon!"
"Isn't it not so unpleasant, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not in agreement with Nyssi; he seemed less dark than usual and had planted his claws into Thassalin's back, to the point of making the Thraki bleed, but evidently, he didn't care much about it. Nevertheless, Thassalin had realized he had terrified his new friends and found a clearing to land.
"MY APOLOGIES, I SMELLED A Scent. I HAD TO CHECK."
"Did you have to drag us here with you?" Tenuk shouted as he slid down Thassalin's back along his tail. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our great and strong fighter! How is he going to catch up with us?"
" He will find a way," retorted Nissy. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Okay, but does Retvik know how to drive?"
Nissy blinked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn’t have a truck like you, and I’ve never seen him drive anything like Kayel’s cute little car either. And if he started coming to work by car, it’s only because YOU drove us there. He just has this bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly burst into laughter, and no one understood why he was laughing. It took him far too long to regain his composure.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR BIG FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A TINY BIKE INTENDED FOR CHILDREN OF TEMTHAN. IT WAS SO FUNNY! I WOULD HAVE LOVED TO HAVE TELEPATHY. IT'S A PRECIOUS THOUGHT! ONE I CANNOT SHARE!"
Kayel laughed, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's right. But what did you pick up, and why did you take off so quickly?"
Thassalin grunted, took off, and vanished briefly before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a rare golden and white dragon-like creature. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI DEMANDS. THE CREATURES ARE NEAR."
The mighty Thraki froze suddenly. Nyssi and Kayel too, their attention drawn to an opening in the clearing. Something large and black was staring at them, whistling. Whatever it was, it opened two massive pairs of wings and dove straight at Thassalin, without sparing the three smaller beings on its path. Kayel and Tenuk managed to take cover just in time, but Nyssi was dragged along and nearly thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the attack by grabbing Nyssi and throwing her onto his back, using his tail's extraordinary length and dexterity, before taking off. The two-winged black creature rushed quickly after them.
Kayel exhaled as he drew the rifle from his back, then opened a pouch in which there was a belt of ammunition. He slung it across his body to have easy access to it, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, would you like to turn into something that can fly?" asked Kayel.
"Would you like to chase them?"
"Of course!"
"but one of them is a giant monster!"
"And so what? I have an ultra-powerful rifle in my hands right now, ready to use. I just need to see him to shoot him."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to clear some space. With a weak, slightly pained grunt, his body expanded, his fur was replaced by scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He quickly reverted back to his normal light blue Thraki form, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Having regained a more normal Thraki appearance, Tenuk now had his back covered in scale plates, but a pair of spikes had also grown on top, useful for Kayel to grip. Tenuk needed a little time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and attempted a pursuit.
However, Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid it.
I suppose it's the other big scary monster that was worrying Lanex? Kayel furrowed his brow as he tried to shoot the second creature, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tenuk didn't react. He was too focused on his flight toward Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature pursuing them. Kayel awkwardly spun around himself in order to face the monster. The fact that it was chasing them was an advantage for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots passed through the creature's upper wings, and it howled in pain before disappearing again beneath the trees. Kayel didn't know if it was still following them, but it would certainly not be able to catch up.
Further away, Nyssi clung desperately as Thassalin flew in circles, firing bursts of flames at the blackened monster. Although the creature was clearly wounded, it seemed furious and determined to fight on, and the fireballs did not seem to have the desired effect. When Thassalin straightened up, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw her weapon, a reliable rifle. It was of course not intended for this kind of situation, but a volley of shots would surely at least discourage the black beast, wouldn't it?
